<h2>The weather in September 2018</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
Daily minimum temperatures were slightly below to 1981-2010 average in Western Europe and Ireland (Figure 5). In the rest of Europe the minimum temperatures were higher than normal, especially in the Mediterranean countries. The maximum temperatures were higher than normal, apart from the UK and the western part of Scandinavia. The coldest nights occurred in Romania and in the north of Scandinavia (Figure 6). In Southern Spain the low temperatures of the coldest night were much above the average.
<br><br>
Svalbard airport (Arctic) has not registered a single month with monthly temperatures below the normals (1961-1990) since November 2010, that is 94 months in a row, see <a href="https://www.met.no/publikasjoner/met-info/_/attachment/download/21578947-fc36-4ca2-9c21-5968dc0c7375:a593521c8d526ac25c46cb97048cadbf34347f5c/MET-info-09-2018.pdf" target="_blank">MET-info 09-2018"</a>.
